To track the status of a route for token exchange, you can use the getRouteStatus method of the LancaClient object. This method allows you to retrieve the current status of the route, including any updates or changes that have occurred during the exchange process.const routeStatus = await lancaClient.getRouteStatus(
	&#x27;0x231b5f78e90bf71996fd65a05c93a0d0fdb562a2cd8eb6944a833c80bae39b3e&#x27;,
)This is just a basic example to get you started. For more information on the Lanca SDK and its features, please refer to the rest of the documentation.

